HEADWORD: Inspeximus
<hw>In*spex"i*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., we have
inspected.]</ety> <def>The first word of ancient charters in England,
confirming a grant made by a former king; hence, a royal
grant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

